#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/input_devices.rst:36
msgid "Exceptions from the Rule"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/input_devices.rst:38
msgid ""
"Unfortunately there are a few corner cases where action and selection might "
"intertwine. Some parts in Blender even violate the principle such that "
":kbd:`LMB` selects and :kbd:`RMB` takes action, for example, the "
":doc:`Outliner </editors/outliner>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/input_devices.rst:44
